00:09:26.110 --> 00:09:27.410
&gt;&gt; Ron Elving: The tapes.

00:09:27.410 --> 00:09:28.710
They always come back.

00:09:28.710 --> 00:09:30.950
&gt;&gt; John Farrell: -- to tail
and to tap the Republican,

00:09:30.950 --> 00:09:33.720
Claire Chennault, the
Republican envoy;

00:09:33.720 --> 00:09:40.990
Anna Chennault the Republican envoy
and the South Vietnamese Embassy

00:09:40.990 --> 00:09:43.920
and the presidential
palace in Saigon.

00:09:43.920 --> 00:09:46.160
So Johnson is getting
all this information

00:09:46.160 --> 00:09:47.960
and he sees what's happening.

00:09:47.960 --> 00:09:50.480
He gets on the phone call
with Republican Senators

00:09:50.480 --> 00:09:53.960
like Everett Dirkson, and he sees,
"I'm reading their hand Everett,"

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:57.030
and this is darn near treason.

00:09:57.030 --> 00:10:01.600
So he confronts Nixon
and Nixon denies it,

00:10:01.600 --> 00:10:06.480
but it has actually happened and
the great tragedy of this story is

00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:09.360 position:56%
that there really was a peace feeler

00:10:09.360 --> 00:10:12.440
from the Soviet Union
to Johnson that summer.

00:10:12.440 --> 00:10:16.380
And the Soviets said, "If you'll
do a bombing halt, we can promise

00:10:16.380 --> 00:10:18.300 position:56%
