00:10:18.300 --> 00:10:20.200
We'll get the North
Vietnamese to the table."

00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:23.740
So what Nixon saw as a dirty trick,

00:10:23.740 --> 00:10:28.110
Johnson actually believed was a
chance to end the war earlier,

00:10:28.110 --> 00:10:32.380
but Nixon intercedes and the
South Vietnamese pull back

00:10:32.380 --> 00:10:35.480
and the peace talks don't happen,
and Nixon is elected in one

00:10:35.480 --> 00:10:38.990
of the closest elections
in American history.

00:10:38.990 --> 00:10:40.720
&gt;&gt; Ron Elving: Forty-three
percent of the vote I believe.

00:10:40.720 --> 00:10:44.050
&gt;&gt; John Farrell: With
only 43% of the vote.

00:10:44.050 --> 00:10:47.030
So elements of this story
come out over the years,

00:10:47.030 --> 00:10:49.870
but Nixon always denied
it and if you go back

00:10:49.870 --> 00:10:53.410
and watch the famous
Frost/Nixon interviews,

00:10:53.410 --> 00:10:57.020 position:56%
David Frost asks him specifically,
